title: MQM’s Shariq Ali wins PS- 90 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Muttahida Qaumi Movement (MQM), Shariq Ali has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-90, Korangi-I, by securing 35,609 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Waqas Iqbal, Independent Candidate, who bagged vote 32,645.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 42.66 %.
